Prisoner's Defence. I went to the shop of Mr. Wicks to buy some leather; he asked me if I did not come there to buy some last week? I said No. He said I did, and brought a woman with me, and that we stole some leather, and I was given in custody and taken to Guildhall, where the boy (
Thomas Wicks
) saw me, and came forward andcharged me with robbing his shop. I deny most solemnly having ever been at the shop, nor had I been in Golden-lane for weeks before.
